|- bgcolor="#efefef" Rudolph was born Laurence Bianca in Brooklyn, NY in 1949.  He attended the High School of Art and Design where he exhibited a wonderful talent for writing Gothic horror stories and detailed draftsmanship.  He championed a folk singer who wrote original tunes, then went off to Europe to develop himself in the artist in exile tradition.  After true dedication to studying his biographical subject, director Ed Wood, he finally receive some of the recognition long due.
